            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220417-38-person408">
                  REBECCA 
                  NEWSAM
               <interp inst="t18220417-38-person408" type="surname" value="NEWSAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-38-person408" type="given" value="REBECCA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-38-person408" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of 
               <persName id="t18220417-38-person409">
                  William 
                  Newsam
               <interp inst="t18220417-38-person409" type="surname" value="Newsam"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-38-person409" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-38-person409" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , my son's name is James; he is eleven years old. On Saturday night, about nine o'clock, the 30th of March, I gave him a sovereign in a box, and sent him on an errand.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220417-38-person410">
                  JAMES 
                  NEWSAM
               <interp inst="t18220417-38-person410" type="surname" value="NEWSAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-38-person410" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-38-person410" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My mother gave me a sovereign in a tin box to pay to Mrs. Powell, of Long-alley, Shoreditch - as I went along I met Powell's son - I knew the prisoner before, he lived in the neighbourhood, I did not see the prisoner near me then. I told Powell what I was going to do; he asked where I was going and I heard him say to the prisoner,</p>
               <p>"I shall run up Angel-alley" - he went away and then the prisoner came and punched me first on the back with his fist, and then put his hand in my pocket and took the sovereign and box out - he took the money first, pushed me, and ran up Angel-alley. I used to call him 
               <persName id="t18220417-38-person411">
                  Billy 
                  Button
               <interp inst="t18220417-38-person411" type="surname" value="Button"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-38-person411" type="given" value="Billy"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-38-person411" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I had seen him talking to Powell, but did not hear what they said - I heard him tell him I was going to pay his mother 5 s. I am sure he is the boy.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220417-38-person412">
                  JAMES 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18220417-38-person412" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-38-person412" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-38-person412" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I apprehended him four days after this.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was not there all that night.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 14.</p>
               <p>Of <rs id="t18220417-38-verdict198" type="verdictDescription">
